+﻿# Email Layout Shells — Delivery
+
+Five table-based, token-driven HTML email **layout shells**. Each section is a labeled
+placeholder ("[ CHART ]", "[ BODY TEXT ]", etc.) that your system fills with real content
+and brand values at runtime via find-and-replace.
+
+## Files
+
+| File | Layout |
+|------|--------|
+| `shell-single.html`  | header → hero stat → visual slot → body text → CTA → footer |
+| `shell-two-col.html` | header → hero number → [ body text \| chart/map slot ] → footer |
+| `shell-digest.html`  | header → section 1 → divider → section 2 → divider → section 3 → footer |
+| `shell-alert.html`   | header → full-width callout → single stat → CTA → footer |
+| `shell-report.html`  | header → title → full-width chart slot → two-col stat row → source line → footer |
+
+`/previews/` contains token-filled sample renders and `/previews/screenshots/`
+holds desktop (600px) and mobile (375px) browser screenshots of each shell.
+
+## Rules met
+
+- Inline CSS only — no `<style>` blocks, no CSS classes, no external fonts, no JavaScript
+- Table-based layout throughout
+- Max width 600px; fluid down to 375px (mobile-readable)
+- Outlook desktop 2016+ via MSO conditional ghost tables + `bgcolor` attributes
+- Gmail web compatible
+- Two-column rows (`shell-two-col`, `shell-report`) stack on mobile **without media queries**
+  (hybrid `inline-block` + ghost-table technique — required because `<style>` blocks aren't allowed)
+- No hardcoded colors, fonts, or strings — every value is a token
+
+## Token system (17 tokens — same find-and-replace pattern across all files)
+
+| Token | Meaning |
+|-------|---------|
+| `{{PRIMARY}}` | main brand color |
+| `{{ACCENT}}` | secondary brand color |
+| `{{SURFACE}}` | card/container background |
+| `{{TEXT}}` | body text color |
+| `{{FONT_FAMILY}}` | font stack, e.g. `'Inter', sans-serif` |
+| `{{BORDER_RADIUS}}` | corner radius, e.g. `12px` |
+| `{{COMPANY_NAME}}` | company name string |
+| `{{LOGO_URL}}` | image src URL for logo |
+| `{{TAGLINE}}` | one-line tagline under logo |
+| `{{WEBSITE_URL}}` | footer link URL |
+| `{{SENDER_NAME}}` | email from name |
+| `{{SENDER_ADDRESS}}` | email from address |
+| `{{DISCLAIMER}}` | footer legal text |
+| `{{MAP_URL}}` | image src URL for map/visual (available in all 5 shells) |
+
+## Tokens used per file
+
+| Token | single | two-col | digest | alert | report |
+|-------|:--:|:--:|:--:|:--:|:--:|
+| `{{PRIMARY}}`        | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{ACCENT}}`         | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{SURFACE}}`        | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{TEXT}}`           | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{FONT_FAMILY}}`    | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{BORDER_RADIUS}}`  | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{COMPANY_NAME}}`   | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{LOGO_URL}}`       | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{TAGLINE}}`        | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{WEBSITE_URL}}`    | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{SENDER_NAME}}`    | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{SENDER_ADDRESS}}` | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{DISCLAIMER}}`     | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+| `{{MAP_URL}}`        | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
+
+All 14 tokens appear in every shell, so one find-and-replace pass works on any file.
+
+## Notes / assumptions to confirm
+
+1. **Placeholder slots use tokens, not hardcoded gray.** To honor the "no hardcoded
+   values anywhere" rule, each placeholder box uses a `{{SURFACE}}` fill with a dashed
+   `{{PRIMARY}}` border and a `{{TEXT}}` label, rather than a literal light-gray. It still
+   reads clearly as an empty slot. Easy to swap to a fixed gray if you prefer.
+
+2. **Color pairings.** Per the original `email-hero` spec, hero/stat blocks use a
+   `{{PRIMARY}}` background with `{{TEXT}}` on top. CTA buttons use `{{ACCENT}}` background
+   with `{{SURFACE}}` as the label color. These assume `{{PRIMARY}}`/`{{ACCENT}}` have
+   enough contrast against `{{TEXT}}`/`{{SURFACE}}`. If your brand colors are very light or
+   very dark, adding one optional `{{ON_PRIMARY}}` text token would make contrast bulletproof.
+
+3. **Outlook degradation (expected, not a bug):** rounded corners (`border-radius`) and
+   `opacity` are ignored by Outlook desktop's Word engine — corners render square and muted
+   text renders full-strength. Layout, colors, and content are unaffected.
+
+4. **`{{MAP_URL}}`** is wired into every shell's primary image slot. Point it at any image
+   (e.g. a Mapbox static URL or a chart PNG).
+
+5. **Previews are browser-rendered** (Chromium) at 600px and 375px, for layout confirmation.
+   Native Gmail/Outlook screenshots can be captured after sign-off.
